comments.body:
@pe224 I noticed the $ prompt in your pasted output. Are you running these commands on a WSL prompt? Are you running any special thirdparty terminal prompt? Do you see the same problem in Windows Terminal (using Powershell prompt), powershell.exe (classic powershell prompt), or cmd.exe (classic DOS prompt)?

Are you running a virus/malware scanner of some form? If so, if you have the ability to turn it off, do you see the problem?

The error basically means that the file descriptor for a pipe which is created through the standard golang exec function has been terminated, which is very unusual but could happen if something was intercepting and blocking process exec calls.
